entry.def: If one thing overlaps another, or if you overlap them, a part of the first thing occupies the same area as a part of the other thing. You can also say that two things overlap .

example.ex: When the bag is folded flat, the bag bottom overlaps one side of the bag...
example.tran: 袋子平整折起后，底面与一侧交叠。

example.ex: Overlap the slices carefully so there are no gaps...
example.tran: 将切片小心翼翼地搭好，中间不留任何空隙。

entry.tran: （在主题、人物、时间等上）（与…）部分相同，（与…）部分交叉
entry.def: If one idea or activity overlaps another, or overlaps with another, they involve some of the same subjects, people, or periods of time.

example.ex: Elizabeth met other Oxford intellectuals some of whom overlapped Naomi's world...
example.tran: 伊丽莎白结识了其他一些牛津大学的学者，其中有几位娜奥米也认识。

example.ex: Christian holy week overlaps with the beginning of the Jewish holiday of Passover...
example.tran: 基督教的圣周与犹太教逾越节的头几天重叠。
